The paper deals with the application of deep learning in analyzing microscopic histopathology images for breast cancer diagnosis. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of attention-based multiple instance learning (A-MIL) for localization, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of visualization techniques, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to the paper.
